						               													<description>June 6, 1944, midnight, the day of the Normandy landing operations. Orders are given to the elite members of the 101st Airborne Division to destroy a radio tower installed in a French village occupied by the Germans. You lead eight paratroopers to this village, where the Germans are advancing an unimaginable plan!&amp;#227;&amp;#128;&amp;#128;The time limit is 6 hours. Will you be able to blow up the radio tower and stop the German army's top-secret plan by then?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Longest Day of the Dead is a solitaire horror wargame. The player first performs paratroopers actions on the outdoor map, and then heads to the village of Nonette while gathering information. In Nonette, he aims to accomplish his mission with the members of his team who survived the battles up to that point. Are the Germans aiming for zombies, immortal soldiers, or even the development of a flying saucer weapon?&amp;#227;&amp;#128;&amp;#128;This is a game with a B-movie (or is it Z?) flavor, with romance, explosions, and even the Beast of G&amp;eacute;vaudan.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is a game published in the Japanese Banzai Magazine EX vol. 4 (2020).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
